`test/widgets/calendar_view_test.dart` do not reproduce on this project's
actual toolchain. This review ran tests via a hardcoded path,
`/home/harsha/flutter/flutter/bin/flutter`, which resolves to a separate,
stale local **Flutter 3.41.1** install whose cached engine/framework shader
artifacts are out of sync with each other — `ink_sparkle.frag` is Flutter's
built-in Material ripple shader, unrelated to any code in this repo.

- The project's configured toolchain is the mise-managed **Flutter 3.44.5**
  (what `which flutter` resolves to, and what this repo's own test/analyze
  skills use).
- Both flagged test files pass cleanly (29/29) under Flutter 3.44.5.
- `.github/workflows/ci.yml` uses `subosito/flutter-action@v2` with
  `channel: stable`, which fetches a fresh stable SDK at CI time — the real
  CI gate never touches the stale local 3.41.1 cache that produced this
  finding.

No code change was made in response to this finding. The stray 3.41.1
install at `/home/harsha/flutter/flutter` was left as-is (outside repo scope,
may be used by other local projects) — if it keeps producing this class of
false positive, repairing it (`flutter precache --force` / `flutter clean`)
or removing the hardcoded path from future reviews would prevent recurrence.

